ard%20Consolidated%20PBY-5A%20Catalina%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64dd0cd2bd8c0900184e4e40%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22651%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20PBY-5A%20Catalina%20at%20the%20US%20Coast%20Guard%20station%20in%20the%20French%20Frigate%20Shoals%20in%201953.%3Cp%3EUS%20Coast%20Guard%20Reserve%2FCmdr.%20John%20Redfield%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECatalina%20Aircraft's%20list%20of%20potential%20missions%20is%20ambitious%2C%20but%20the%20original%20Consolidated%20Aircraft%20PBY%20Catalina%20was%20a%20versatile%20plane.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDesigned%20in%20the%20mid-1930s%20as%20a%20US%20Navy%20patrol%20bomber%2C%20the%20%26quot%3BCat%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3BDumbo%26quot%3B%20served%20as%20a%20search%20plane%2C%20anti-submarine%20aircraft%2C%20torpedo%20bomber%2C%20rescue%20plane%2C%20and%20troop%20and%20cargo%20carrier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Navy%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fairandspace.si.edu%2Fcollection-objects%2Fconsolidated-pby-5-catalina%2Fnasm_A19730277000%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eordered%20200%3C%2Fa%3E%20PBY-5s%2C%20the%20latest%20version%20of%20the%20aircraft%2C%20in%20December%201939%20but%20would%20acquire%20hundreds%20of%20them%20during%20the%20war.%20With%20more%20powerful%20engines%2C%20the%20PBY-5%20had%20a%20maximum%20speed%20of%20about%20175%20mph%20and%20could%20fly%202%2C545%20miles%20without%20refueling.%20It%20was%20armed%20with%20several%20machine%20guns%20and%20could%20carry%20bombs%2C%20depth%20charges%2C%20or%20torpedoes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20all%2C%20some%204%2C000%20Catalinas%20were%20built%20between%201936%20and%201945%2C%20including%20600%20in%20Canada%20and%2027%20in%20the%20Soviet%20Union.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221846%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Navy%20seaplane%20tender%20Salisbury%20Sound%20Martin%20P5M-1%20Marlin%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6078b22b4206150018175ca8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221175%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20crane%20aboard%20seaplane%20tender%20USS%20Salisbury%20Sound%20lifts%20a%20Martin%20P5M-1%20Marlin%20in%20San%20Diego%20Bay%20in%201957.%3Cp%3EUS%20Navy%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20Catalina's%20World%20War%20II%20feats%20was%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhunt-for-battleship-bismarck-proved-uboats-were-nazis-best-weapon-2021-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elocating%20the%20German%20battleship%20Bismarck%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20enabling%20the%20Royal%20Navy%20to%20close%20in%20and%20sink%20it%2C%20as%20well%20as%20spotting%20approaching%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-is-learning-from-battle-of-midway-world-war-ii-2021-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJapanese%20ships%20at%20the%20Battle%20of%20Midway%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20its%20greatest%20contribution%20was%20as%20an%20anti-submarine%20aircraft%20that%20sank%20German%20and%20Japanese%20submarines%2C%20pinpointed%20them%20for%20Allied%20surface%20ships%20to%20attack%2C%20or%20kept%20the%20subs%20at%20bay%20just%20by%20being%20present.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20serving%20in%20several%20Allied%20militaries%20during%20World%20War%20II%2C%20many%20Catalinas%20remained%20in%20operation%20with%20militaries%20and%20civilian%20users%20around%20the%20world.%20The%20US%20military%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fflying-boats-seaplanes-competition-with-china-in-pacific-2021-4%5C%22%3Epursued%20other%20seaplanes%3C%2Fa%3E%20early%20in%20the%20Cold%20War%2C%20but%20amphibious%20aircraft%20had%20lost%20their%20utility%20by%201960.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20recently%2C%20some%20Catalinas%20were%20used%20as%20firefighting%20aircraft%2C%20though%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.flightglobal.com%2Ffix