ems%2C%20some%20of%20which%20are%20quite%20dark%20and%20twisted%2C%20trace%20the%20lifecycle%20of%20a%20computer%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Morgenthau%20put%20it%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fbooks%2F2023%2F08%2F05%2Fi-am-code-davinci-002-ai-poems%2F%5C%22%3EWashington%20Post%20column%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20%26quot%3BIf%20OpenAI's%20ChatGPT%20models%20are%20its%20star%20pupils%2C%20code-davinci-002%20is%20its%20dropout%20savant%20%E2%80%94%20troubled%2C%20to%20be%20sure%2C%20but%20also%20a%20lot%20more%20interesting.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20trio%20felt%20that%20if%20they%20could%20get%20%26quot%3BI%20Am%20Code%26quot%3B%20into%20Herzog's%20hands%2C%20they%20would%20be%20reaching%20their%20target%20audience%2C%20Katz%20wrote%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flithub.com%2Fi-am-the-only-one-who-should-recite-them-when-werner-herzog-narrates-your-ai-poetry-collection%2F%5C%22%3Epost%20on%20Lit%20Hub.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20book's%20publisher%20made%20contact%20with%20Herzog%2C%20Katz%20managed%20to%20connect%20with%20him%20directly%20over%20email.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20it%20will%20be%20extraordinary%2C%20something%20puzzling%2C%20and%20deep%2C%20and%20never%20experienced%20before.%20Besides%2C%20looking%20at%20the%20poems%20again%2C%20I%20am%20sure%20now%20that%20I%20am%20the%20only%20one%20who%20should%20recite%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Herzog%20responded%2C%20according%20to%20Katz's%20Lit%20Hub%20piece.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKatz%20is%20unclear%20about%20what%20made%20Herzog%20agree%20to%20do%20the%20project%2C%20but%20told%20Insider%20that%20the%20filmmaker%20%26quot%3Bhas%20a%20connection%20with%20these%20poems%20and%20is%20even%20including%20one%20of%20them%20in%20one%20of%20his%20upcoming%20books.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThroughout%20the%20recording%20process%2C%20Herzog%20had%20to%20make%20some%20adjustments%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F08%2F14%2Fstyle%2Fwerner-herzog-ai-poetry.html%3Faction%3Dclick%26module%3DWell%26pgtype%3DHomepage%26section%3DStyle%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%20reported.%3C%2Fa%3E%20He%20initially%20tried%20to%20use%20a%20robotic%20voice%2C%20in%20the%20vein%20of%20Stephen%20Hawking%2C%20before%20taking%20a%20more%20natural%20approach%2C%20he%20told%20the%20Times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20has%20to%20be%20like%20a%20human%20imitating%20a%20human%20completely%2C%20and%20with%20a%20very%20deep%20longing%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20recording%2C%20Herzog%20didn't%20take%20breaks%20to%20eat%20or%20use%20the%20bathroom%2C%20and%20only%20drank%20water%20when%20prompted%2C%20Katz%20wrote%20on%20Lit%20Hub.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOn%20one%20performance%20(I%20forget%20the%20poem)%2C%20he%20was%20so%20happy%20with%20his%20first%20take%20that%20he%20said%2C%20'And%20in%20fact%2C%20I%20refuse%20to%20do%20it%20again%2C'%26quot%3B%20Katz%20told%20Insider%20of%20directing%20Herzog%20during%20recording.%20%26quot%3BI%20liked%20that%20he%20would%20lay%20down%20the%20law%20like%20that%2C%20even%20when%20faced%20with%20zero%20disagreement.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20reproducing%20poetry%20in%20the%20vein%20of%20a%20current%20or%20past%20writer%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20Am%20Code%26quot%3B%20was%20crafted%20by%20encouraging%20code-davinci-002%20to%20write%20poems%20in%20a%20voice%20of%20its%20own.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20models%20are%20trained%20on%20data%20mined%20from%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20internet%20web%20pages%20%E2%80%94%20including%20copyrighted%20material%20from%20authors%2C%20artists%2C%20and%20musicians.%20This%20had%20been%20a%20sticking%20point%2C%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-companies-thousands-authors-demand-compensation-for-using-works-2023-7%5C%22%3E8%2C000%20authors%20signing%20an%20open%20letter%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20July%