ughters.%20It%20is%20the%20latest%20action%20in%20the%20private%20family%20dispute%20that%20is%20increasingly%20public%20as%20the%20sides%20fight%20over%20Blum's%20considerable%20fortune.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKatherine%20Feinstein%2C%20a%20former%20San%20Francisco%20judge%2C%20filed%20the%20suit%20on%20behalf%20of%20her%20mother.%20A%20previous%20suit%20revealed%20that%20Feinstein%20had%20granted%20her%20daughter%20power%20of%20attorney%2C%20though%20it%20was%20not%20clear%20how%20far%20the%20agreement%20extended.%20The%20latest%20suit%2C%20filed%20on%20August%208%2C%20confirms%20that%20Katherine%20Feinstein%20holds%20legal%20power%20of%20attorney.%C2%A0%20The%20agreement%20for%20those%20powers%20was%20made%20on%20July%2023%2C%20per%20the%20legal%20documents.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdianne-feinsteins-daughter-has-power-of-attorney-over-her-2023-8%5C%22%3EThe%20existence%20of%20the%20power%20of%20attorney%20agreement%3C%2Fa%3E%20raised%20speculation%2C%20encouraged%20by%20one%20of%20the%20lawyers%20for%20the%20trustees%2C%20about%20the%20power%20Katherine%20Feinstein%20held%20on%20behalf%20of%20a%20sitting%20US%20senator.%20Based%20on%20the%20new%20information%2C%20it%20is%20possible%20that%20the%20agreement%20was%20brokered%20as%20a%20matter%20of%20convenience%20to%20Feinstein.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFeinstein's%20health%20is%20closely%20followed%20in%20Washington.%20At%2090%2C%20she%20is%20the%20oldest%20member%20of%20the%20Senate.%20Feinstein%20missed%20nearly%20three%20months%20of%20votes%20after%20contracting%20shingles.%20Some%20fellow%20Democrats%20have%20called%20on%20Feinstein%20to%20resign%2C%20but%20thus%20far%20she%20has%20repeatedly%20rebuffed%20such%20requests.%20In%20the%20meantime%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdianne-feinstein-confused-just-say-aye-senate-hearing-video-2023-7%5C%22%3Ereporters%20have%20observed%20multiple%20instances%3C%2Fa%3E%20where%20Feinstein%20appears%20to%20be%20confused%20or%20not%20fully%20aware%20of%20what%20is%20unfolding.%20A%20former%20San%20Francisco%20mayor%2C%20Feinstein%20has%20held%20to%20her%20previous%20promise%20to%20step%20down%20after%20her%20current%20term%20ends%20in%20January%202025.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20last%20week%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdianne-feinstein-hospitalized-after-tripping-at-home-2023-8%5C%22%3EFeinstein%20was%20briefly%20hospitalized%20after%20falling%20at%20her%20home.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20billionaire%20financier%2C%20Blum%20owned%20multiple%20properties%2C%20including%20homes%20in%20California%20and%20Washington%2C%20D.C.%2C%20along%20with%20a%203%2C500-square-foot%20Stinson%20Beach%20house%2C%20and%20an%20ocean-front%20home%20on%20the%20Hawaiian%20island%20of%20Kauai.%20Blum%20also%20reportedly%20owned%20a%20stake%20in%20the%20Claremont%20Hotel%20in%20Berkeley%2C%20California%20that%20was%20reportedly%20sold%20for%20%24163%20million.%20The%20suit%20alleges%20the%20proceeds%20from%20that%20sale%20never%20touched%20Feinstein's%20trust.%20In%20a%20previous%20suit%2C%20Katherine%20Feinstein%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.li%2FuOVz8%23selection-3405.180-3405.185%5C%22%3Ealleged%20that%20the%20trust%20was%20not%20moving%20%3C%2Fa%3Equickly%20enough%C2%A0to%20sell%20the%20Stinson%20Beach%20house.%20The%20suit%20claimed%20Blum's%20daughters%20want%20to%20keep%20the%20property.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22raw%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fembed.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F23911060-katherine-feinstein-suit%2F%3Fembed%3D1%26responsive%3D1%26title%3D1%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22700%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Katherine%20Feinstein%20suit%20(Hosted%20by%20DocumentCloud)%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22905%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20August%20suit%2C%20Feinstein's%20martial%20trust%20should%20have%20already%20received%20%245%20million.%20It%20further%20alleges%20that%20the%20trustees%2C%20Michael%20Klein%2C%20Marc%20Scholvinck%2C%20and%20Verett%20Mims%2C%20failed%20to%20respond%20to%20Feinstein's%20requests%20that%20the%20trust%20reimburse%20her%20medical%20expenses.%20Katherine%20Feinstein%20concedes%20that%20the%20trust%20has%20never%20denied%20one%20of%20Feinstein's%20requests%2C%20but%20characterizes%20this%20claim%20as%20%26quot%3Bmisleading.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Trustees%20have%20failed%20to%20respond%20to%20any%20requests%20for%20disbursements%2C%20which%20is%20a%20de%20facto%20denial%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20suit%20alleges.%20%26quot%3BThe%20Trustees%20have%20engaged%20in%20an%20overarching%20pattern%20of%20inaction%20related%20to%20Senator%20Feinstein's%20beneficial%20interests%2C%20to%20her%20detriment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20attorney%20for%20Klein%20and%20Scholvinck%20slammed%20the%20latest%20suit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20trustees%20have%20acted%20ethically%20and%20appropriately%20at%20all%20times%3B%20the%20same%20cannot%20be%20said%20for%20Katherine%20Feinstein%2C%26quot%3B%20attorney%20Steven%20P.%20Braccini%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%20%26quot%3BThis%20filing%20is%20unconscionable.%20The%20trustees%20have%20always%20respected%20Senator%20Feinstein%20and%20always%20will.%20But%20this%20has%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20her%20needs%20and%20everything%20to%20do%20with%20her%20daughter's%20avarice.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20to%20the%20Chronicle%2C%20Feinstein's%20Senate%20office%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20the%20suit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdianne-feinstein-financial-elder-abuse-blum-trust-lawsuit-california-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692209245000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64dd0584bd8c0900184e421e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%