5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F16133557%2FUntitled-design-1-2.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fjobs%2Fhr-policies-trends%2Fover-17000-indian-startup-employees-laid-off-in-the-first-half-of-2023-as-funding-winter-refuses-to-thaw%2Farticleshow%2F102263696.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E70%20Indian%20start-ups%3C%2Fa%3E%20laid%20off%2017%2C000%20employees%20(including%202%2C500%20people%20at%20EdTech%20firm%20Byju%E2%80%99s)%20in%20the%20first%20six%20months%20of%202023%2C%20much%20newsprint%20and%20digital%20ink%20was%20devoted%20to%20analysing%20what%20it%20meant%20for%20the%20companies%2C%20their%20employees%2C%20the%20start-up%20ecosystem%20and%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECompare%20this%20to%20the%20more%20than%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fhundreds-of-ngos-fcra-licences-no-longer-valid-now%2Farticleshow%2F99017502.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E100%20nonprofits%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20have%20lost%20their%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fidronline.org%2Fidr-explains-fcra%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFCRA%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20seven-month%20period.%20Approximately%204%2C000%20people%20at%20CARE%2C%20one%20of%20the%20larger%20global%20nonprofits%20operating%20in%20India%2C%20were%20reportedly%20rendered%20unemployed%20versus%20the%202%2C500%20people%20at%20Byju%E2%80%99s.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20yet%2C%20there%20is%20no%20conversation%20on%20what%20this%20means%20for%20the%20economy%20%E2%80%93%20nonprofits%20contribute%20to%202%25%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20GDP%3B%20on%20the%20viability%20of%20the%20nonprofits%20themselves%3B%20on%20the%20debilitating%20impact%20on%20their%20staff%2C%20most%20of%20whom%20are%20employed%20in%20the%20smaller%20towns%20and%20villages%3B%20and%2C%20above%20all%2C%20on%20the%20millions%20of%20vulnerable%20families%20that%20are%20now%20deprived%20of%20the%20critical%20services%20these%20organisations%20provide%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20invisible%20sector%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%202012%20report%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Statistics%20and%20Programme%20Implementation%20(MoSPI)%2C%20civil%20society%20organisations%20(CSOs)%20account%20for%2027%20lakh%20jobs%20and%2034%20lakh%20full-time%20volunteers%2C%20generating%20employment%20figures%20higher%20than%20that%20of%20the%20public%20sector.%20In%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fguidestarindia.org%2FIndia_CSO_Reports.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurvey%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20515%20nonprofits%20conducted%20by%20CSO%20Coalition%4075%20and%20anchored%20by%20GuideStar%20India%2C%2047%25%20reported%20that%20they%20are%20the%20biggest%20source%20of%20formal%20employment%20in%20more%20than%20half%20of%20the%20local%20geographies%20that%20they%20work%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20nonprofits%20are%20the%20connectors%20between%20the%20state%20and%20the%20people.%20More%20than%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fguidestarindia.org%2FIndia_CSO_Reports.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E50%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20organisations%20work%20locally%2C%20in%20rural%20areas%20and%20in%20aspirational%20districts.%20They%20work%20on%20education%2C%20health%20and%20nutrition%2C%20livelihoods%2C%20water%20and%20sanitation%2C%20climate%20change%2C%20agriculture%2C%20women%20and%20child%20rights%2C%20disability%2C%20and%20citizen%20engagement%20%E2%80%93%20covering%20every%20aspect%20of%20a%20citizen%E2%80%99s%20life.%20They%20create%20local%20livelihoods%2C%20develop%20skills%2C%20promote%20social%20mobility%2C%20and%20engage%20local%20businesses.%20Half%20of%20the%20nonprofits%20that%20were%20surveyed%20work%20with%20government%20bodies%20(schools%2C%20panchayats%2C%20municipalities%2C%20anganwadis%2C%20and%20primary%20health%20centres)%20and%20self-help%20groups.%20Strengthening%20them%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20accelerates%20local%20area%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENonprofit%20jobs%20are%20not%20like%20those%20in%20the%20business%20and%20government%20sectors.%20As%20a%20leader%20of%20a%20nonprofit%20said%2C%20a%20nonprofit%20worker%E2%80%99s%20role%20is%20to%20bring%20about%20social%20change%3B%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20just%20a%20job.%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20jobs%20are%20lost%2C%20so%20are%20the%20opportunities%20to%20improve%20the%20lives%20of%20the%20marginalised%20and%20vulnerable%20populations%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20impact%20on%20communities%20is%20immediate%20and%20substantial%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDifferent%20kinds%20of%20work%20have%20come%20to%20a%20halt%20due%20to%20the%20FCRA%20cancellations.%20Efforts%20around%20child%20protection%2C%20immunisation%2C%20prevention%20of%20neonatal%20deaths%2C%20provision%20of%20health%20and%20nutrition%20facilities%20in%20schools%20and%20anganwadis%2C%20creating%20material%20for%20teacher%20training%20for%20early%20childhood%20learning%2C%20engaging%20with%20parents%20on%20their%20children%E2%80%99s%20schooling%2C%20providing%20skilling%20and%20livelihood%20opportunities%20for%20the%20young%2C%20enabling%20access%20to%20government%20entitlements%20%E2%80%93%20all%20of%20these%20have%20stopped%20in%20the%20regions%20where%20these%20nonprofits%20were%20operating.%20An%20estimated%204%2C000%20to%208%20lakh%20people%20per%20organisation%20no%20longer%20have%20access%20to%20the%20services%20provided%20by%20these%20nonprofits%20whose%20FCRA%20licences%20have%20been%20cancelled.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeyond%20the%20cessation%20of%20services%2C%20the%20system%20of%20trust%20%E2%80%93%20which%20the%20frontline%20staff%20at%20the%20nonprofits%20have%20spent%20years%20developing%20with%20the%20community%20%E2%80%93%20breaks%20down%3B%20the%20belief%20in%20nonprofits%20as%20enablers%20is%20shaken.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20CEO%20at%20a%20large%20nonprofit%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20not%20about%20just%20one%20organisation%E2%80%99s%20work%20coming%20to%20a%20standstill%3B%20people%20feel%20let%20down%20by%20us.%20Why%20would%20they%20believe%20us%20the%20next%20time%20when%20we%20say%20that%20we%20will%20fulfill%20a%20certain%20commitment%20over%20a%20certain%20period%20of%20time%3F%E2%80%9D%20he%20asks.%20This%20loss%20of%20trust%20is%20hard%20to%20reverse%2C%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Ffcra-licenses-400-ngos-invalid%5C%22%3EIn%20Past%20Seven%20Months%2C%20Nearly%20400%20NGOs%20Lost%20Validity%20of%20FCRA%20Licenses%3A%20Report%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20invisible%20workforce%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20communities%20are%20left%20at%20a%20loose%20end%2C%20the%20frontline%20workers%C2%A0%20%E2%80%93%20the%20people%20who%20are%20employees%20of%20these%20nonprofits%20%E2%80%93%20and%20their%20families%20are%20severely%20impacted%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20the%20frontline%20staff%20who%20have%20lost%20their%20jobs%20are%20typically%20graduates%20or%2C%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20people%20with%20post%20graduate%20degrees.%20They%20are%20anchored%20in%20their%20community%2C%20and%20most%20of%20them%20have%20chosen%20to%20stay%20in%20that%20village%20or%20town.%20Their%20livelihood%20and%20strength%20is%20in%20and%20around%20the%20local%20ecosystem.%20According%20to%20the%20nonprofit%20CEO%2C%20these%20individuals%20are%20the%20first-mile%20connectors%20and%20integrators%20there%3B%20they%20are%20deeply%20rooted%20in%20and%20valuable%20to%20the%20community.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20also%20means%20that%20these%20field%20staff%20need%20nonprofits%20to%20keep%20them%20there%2C%20and%20we%20nonprofits%20need%20them%20for%20the%20work%20we%20do%20with%20communities%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20adds%20that%20there%20are%20limited%20employment%20opportunities%20in%20the%20areas%20where%20most%20of%20the%20rural%20community%20mobilisers%20live.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20the%20fruits%20of%20development%20such%20as%20industry%20and%20other%20livelihood%20opportunities%20had%20reached%20these%20areas%2C%20these%20individuals%20would%20have%20had%20multiple%20employment%20options.%20What%20we%E2%80%99ve%20seen%20over%20the%20years%20is%20that%20development%20work%20is%20one%20of%20the%20last%20choices%20for%20most%20people%E2%80%94they%20would%20prefer%20a%20government%20job%20or%20some%20private%20enterprise%20because%20there%20is%20better%20compensation%2C%20continuity%2C%20and%20certainty%20of%20income.%E2%80%9D%20This%20FCRA%20cancellation%20and%20sudden%20loss%20of%20jobs%20has%20reinforced%20the%20precarity%20of%20working%20for%20a%20nonprofit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENo%20jobs%20in%20the%20market%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeema%20Muskan%20is%20a%2035-year-old%2C%20Patna-based%20researcher%20who%20used%20to%20work%20with%20a%20nonprofit.%C2%A0%20She%20has%20more%20than%2015%20years%20of%20experience%20in%20the%20fields%20of%20health%2C%20education%2C%20and%20nutrition.%20When%20the%20nonprofit%20she%20worked%20with%20lost%20its%20FCRA%20licence%20in%20March%202023%2C%20she%20lost%20her%20job%2C%20and%20with%20that%20her%20sense%20of%20identity%20and%20financial%20independence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Seema%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20easy%20to%20find%20another%20job.%20%E2%80%9CEveryone%E2%80%99s%20FCRA%20is%20at%20risk.%20The%20belief%20among%20all%20the%20other%20nonprofits%20is%20that%20they%20are%20next%20in%20line%20to%20lose%20their%20FCRA%20licences.%20The%20fear%20is%20so%20entrenched%20that%20they%20aren%E2%80%99t%20hiring%20either.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeema%20says%20there%20are%20probably%20some%20options%20with%20other%20large%20nonprofits%20in%20states%20such%20as%20Chhattisgarh%20and%20Jharkhand.%20But%20she%20needs%20to%20be%20in%20Patna%20because%20of%20her%20family%3B%20her%20husband%2C%20children%2C%20and%20in-laws%20are%20there.%20%E2%80%9CI%20have%20two%20young%20kids%2C%20aged%20five%20and%20eight%20years.%20I%20can%E2%80%99t%20leave%20them%20behind%20to%20go%20work%20in%20another%20town%20or%20city.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20you%20have%20a%20job%2C%20you%20have%20an%20identity%2C%20a%20sense%20of%20self%20in%20society%2C%20you%20have%20independence%2C%20your%20own%20money%2C%20and%20you%20contribute%20to%20your%20kids%E2%80%99%20education%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%20Seema%20contributed%20to%20the%20repayment%20of%20their%20fairly%20large%20home%20loan%2C%20as%20well%20as%20their%20children%E2%80%99s%20education.%20Now%20she%20fears%20what%20this%20lack%20of%20income%20means%20for%20her%20family%E2%80%99s%20financial%20stability.%20%E2%80%9CYou%20can%20reduce%20your%20expenses%20significantly%2C%20you%20can%20cut%20down%20on%20many%20things%2C%20but%20the%20one%20thing%20you%20can%E2%80%99t%20do%20is%20stop%20your%20children%E2%80%99s%20education.%20And%20now%20that%20seems%20like%20a%20looming%20possibility%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeema%20does%2C%20however%2C%20believe%20that%20her%20male%20colleagues%20have%20it%20worse.%20%E2%80%9CEven%20if%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20a%20job%2C%20at%20least%20there%20is%20some%20money%20coming%20in%20because%20of%20my%20husband%E2%80%99s%20business.%20For%20many%20of%20my%20colleagues%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20far%20worse%20because%20they%20are%20the%20primary%20breadwinners%3B%20their%20families%20depend%20on%20them.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20GuideStar%20India%20survey%2C%2064%25%20of%20the%20nonprofits%20surveyed%20said%20that%20their%20employees%20are%20the%20sole%20breadwinners%20in%20their%20respective%20families.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDinesh%20Kumar%E2%80%99s%20entire%20career%20has%20been%20in%20the%20social%20sector.%20With%2018%20years%20of%20experience%2C%20he%20has%20worked%20in%20education%2C%20on%20child%20protection%20and%20nutrition%2C%20and%20with%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fidronline.org%2Fpower-to-the-people-the-journey-of-panchayati-raj-institutions%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPanchayati%20Raj%20institutions%3C%2Fa%3E.%20At%20his%20previous%20nonprofit%2C%20his%20work%20entailed%20helping%20vulnerable%20populations%20access%20any%20of%20the%2040%E2%80%9350%20government%20schemes%20that%20they%20and%20their%20families%20were%20eligible%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDinesh%20says%20that%20few%20other%20organisations%20do%20the%20work%20that%20his%20nonprofit%20does%2C%20and%20there%20are%20limited%20opportunities%20for%20someone%20with%20his%20skills%20and%20knowledge.%20%E2%80%9CMy%20professional%20career%20has%20been%20in%20the%20social%20sector.%20I%20have%20worked%20for%2018%20years%20and%20built%20considerable%20skills%20working%20with%20communities%2C%20helping%20with%20data%20collection%2C%20managing%20large%20research%20surveys%2C%20and%20conducting%20training%20and%20facilitation.%20But%20if%20other%20nonprofits%20also%20stop%20hiring%2C%20where%20will%20we%20go%2C%20how%20will%20we%20survive%3F%E2%80%9D%20he%20asks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Funion-home-ministry-fcra-ngos-disability%5C%22%3EMHA%20Decision%20Strips%20Six%20Prominent%20Disability%2C%20Human%20Rights%20NGOs%20of%20FCRA%20Licences%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EToo%20many%20people%2C%20too%20few%20jobs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20many%20of%20the%20frontline%20staff%2C%20applying%20for%20and%20getting%20a%20new%20job%20comes%20with%20its%20share%20of%20challenges.%20Dinesh%20says%20that%20even%20as%20he%20circulates%20his%20resume%2C%20he%20knows%20that%20the%20chances%20are%20low.%20Unemployment%20is%20already%20high%20across%20the%20country.%20In%20most%20cases%2C%20his%20resume%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20get%20shortlisted%20because%20of%20his%20specialised%20skills.%20Other%20nonprofits%20that%20might%20leverage%20his%20skills%20aren%E2%80%99t%20hiring%2C%20or%20if%20they%20are%20they%20have%20far%20too%20many%20applicants.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20for%20many%2C%20the%20process%20of%20application%20itself%20is%20hard.%20Mukesh%20Kumar%20was%20a%20district%20academic%20fellow%20with%20CARE%20before%20he%20lost%20his%20job%20in%20June%202023.%20Starting%20off%20at%20a%20low-paid%20position%20in%20a%20large%20education%20nonprofit%20almost%2012%20years%20ago%2C%20he%20has%20risen%20to%20be%20a%20district-level%20coordinator.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMukesh%20has%20been%20speaking%20to%20his%20networks%20in%20the%20sector%2C%20scouring%20DevNet%20and%20LinkedIn%20for%20any%20open%20positions%2C%20and%20even%20googling%20jobs%20in%20his%20district.%20The%20problem%20is%20compounded%20by%20the%20lack%20of%20access%20to%20computers%20or%20laptops.%20%E2%80%9CWhile%20technology%20might%20have%20advanced%20and%20is%20easily%20accessible%20now%2C%20I%20have%20no%20means%20to%20buy%20a%20computer.%20This%20means%20that%20when%20I%20get%20the%20test%20assignments%20that%20organisations%20give%20as%20part%20of%20their%20recruitment%20process%2C%20I%20have%20to%20either%20type%20the%20answers%20on%20my%20mobile%20phone%20(which%20is%20extremely%20hard%20to%20do)%20or%20write%20them%20down%20by%20hand%2C%20scan%20the%20document%2C%20and%20then%20e-mail%20it%20to%20them%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Mukesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDinesh%20adds%20that%20he%20would%20like%20to%20keep%20working%20in%20the%20social%20sector%2C%20but%20might%20not%20really%20have%20a%20choice.%20%E2%80%9CUnlike%20the%20government%20and%20private%20sector%2C%20our%20salaries%20don%E2%80%99t%20allow%20for%20savings.%20I%20have%20enjoyed%20working%20in%20the%20social%20sector%2C%20building%20relationships%20with%20the%20community%2C%20and%20helping%20people%20get%20their%20entitlements%20and%20what%20is%20due%20to%20them.%20I%20want%20to%20continue%20working%20in%20this%20space%20and%20contribute%20to%20society%2C%20but%20now%20I%20have%20nothing%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMukesh%20reiterates%20the%20deep%20trust%20and%20relationships%20he%20has%20built%20with%20the%20community.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20work%20closely%20with%20families%20to%20make%20sure%20they%20know%20what%E2%80%99s%20happening%20in%20the%20schools%2C%20and%20whether%20their%20children%20have%20access%20to%20quality%20education.%20We%20understand%20the%20gaps%20in%20the%20education%20system%2C%20and%20so%20we%20provide%20training%20for%20government%20staff%20as%20needed%2C%20facilitate%20parent%E2%80%93teacher%20interactions%2C%20help%20parents%20understand%20how%20their%20kids%20should%20be%20treated%2C%20and%20so%20on.%20People%20trust%20us%20because%20they%20know%20we%20are%20doing%20it%20for%20their%20benefit.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhere%20can%20they%20go%20now%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExcept%20for%20the%20big%20corporate%20foundations%20that%20implement%20programmes%20themselves%2C%20have%20large%20teams%2C%20and%20are%20well%20funded%2C%20most%20of%20the%20nonprofits%20cannot%20help%20because%20a)%20they%20are%20short%20of%20resources%20themselves%20and%20have%20no%20funds%20to%20spare%2C%20and%20b)%20they%20are%20afraid%20of%20losing%20their%20FCRA%20licences%20and%20what%20that%20will%20mean%20for%20their%20own%20employees%20and%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDinesh%20adds%20that%20people%20have%20been%20advising%20him%20to%20start%20a%20business.%20%E2%80%9CBut%20businesses%20take%20five%20to%2010%20years%20to%20take%20off.%20I%E2%80%99m%20already%2040%20years%20old.%20I%20will%20be%2050%20by%20the%20time%20I%20get%20somewhere%20in%20business.%20And%20how%20will%20I%20manage%20in%20the%20meantime%2C%20with%20my%20kids%20growing%20up%20and%20the%20increasing%20expenses%3F%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Mukesh%2C%20the%20situation%20is%20so%20dire%20that%20he%20has%20been%20working%20as%20a%20mechanic%20for%20the%20last%20couple%20of%20weeks.%20Like%20Seema%20and%20Dinesh%2C%20he%20has%20extensive%20skills%20in%20education%2C%20training%20and%20facilitation%2C%20relationship%20building%2C%20and%20communications%2C%20most%20of%20which%20feel%20redundant%20to%20him%20right%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMy%20friends%20laugh%20at%20me%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%20%E2%80%9CBut%20what%20option%20do%20I%20have%3F%20I%E2%80%99m%2035%20years%20old%3B%20I%20have%20a%20wife%2C%20three%20kids%2C%20and%20old%20parents%20to%20support.%20I%20used%20to%20get%20Rs%2021%2C500%20in%20hand%20monthly.%20Given%20that%20I%20have%20had%20no%20job%20for%20a%20few%20months%20now%20and%20I%E2%80%99m%20the%20sole%20provider%20for%20the%20family%2C%20I%20have%20no%20money%20left%20at%20all.%20The%20future%20looks%20very%20dark.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20executive%20director%20of%20a%20leading%20nonprofit%2C%20which%20works%20extensively%20with%20rural%20communities%2C%20says%20that%20with%20so%20many%20FCRA%20licences%20being%20cancelled%20and%20the%20resultant%20loss%20of%20jobs%2C%20there%20is%20a%20high%20chance%20that%20people%20will%20look%20for%20work%20outside%20the%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%E2%80%99m%20afraid%20companies%20are%20going%20to%20take%20undue%20advantage%20of%20these%20frontline%20workers%E2%80%99%20financial%20distress%20and%20offer%20them%20roles%20like%20recovery%20agents%20for%20gold%20and%20other%20loans.%20The%20close%20relationships%20they%20have%20built%20with%20the%20communities%20are%20likely%20to%20be%20misused%20by%20these%20financial%20companies%20to%20recover%20money%20%E2%80%93%20a%20sharp%20contrast%20to%20the%20spirit%20of%20service%20that%20most%20of%20these%20frontline%20staff%20have%20worked%20with%20within%20their%20communities%20till%20date%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESetting%20the%20country%20back%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDinesh%20says%20that%20organisations%20like%20the%20one%20he%20worked%20for%20raised%20a%20voice%20for%20the%20%3Cem%3Eaam%20aadmi%3C%2Fem%3E.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20made%20sure%20they%20could%20access%20their%20rights%20and%20entitlements%2C%20whether%20it%20was%20a%20scholarship%20or%20a%20widow%E2%80%99s%20pension%20or%20a%20child%E2%80%99s%20birth%20certificate.%20Who%20will%20speak%20for%20them%20now%2C%20who%20will%20take%20their%20voices%20to%20the%20powers%20that%20be%3F%E2%80%9D%20he%20asks.%20%E2%80%9CBy%20shutting%20us%20down%2C%20they%20are%20shutting%20down%20the%20voice%20of%20the%20common%20people%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMukesh%20says%20that%20the%20people%20had%20faith%20in%20them.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20knew%20we%20were%20working%20for%20them.%20They%20could%20count%20on%20us%20to%20help%20them%20get%20their%20rightful%20entitlements%20from%20the%20state%2C%20to%20look%20after%20the%20interest%20of%20their%20children%20when%20it%20came%20to%20education%20and%20healthcare%2C%20and%20to%20be%20a%20bridge%20between%20them%20and%20the%20government.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20nonprofit%20CEO%2C%20if%20you%20lose%20these%20people%20who%20are%20the%20connectors%20to%20the%20communities%2C%20you%20remove%20visibility%20to%20the%20people%20on%20the%20margins.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20these%20nonprofits%20and%20their%20field%20staff%20who%20push%20for%20and%20enable%20the%20idea%20of%20participatory%20democracy%20in%20our%20country%20%E2%80%93%20by%20offering%20vulnerable%20populations%20access%20to%20the%20state%2C%20platforms%2C%20and%20means%20to%20address%20their%20issues%2C%20while%20also%20strengthening%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20services%20to%20them.%20Without%20them%2C%20there%20is%20no%20active%20citizenship%20and%20we%20will%20regress%20to%20the%20past%20where%20these%20communities%20had%20no%20power%20or%20say%20in%20our%20democracy.%20So%2C%20instead%20of%20looking%20at%202047%2C%20as%20an%20idea%20of%20a%20developed%20country%2C%20we%E2%80%99ll%20be%20looking%20at%20a%20setback%20of%20another%2025%20years%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20originally%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fidronline.org%2Farticle%2Ffundraising-and-communications%2Fwho-loses-when-fcra-licences-get-cancelled%2F%5C%22%3Epublished%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fidronline.org%2F%5C%22%3EIDR%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692174643000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F16133557%2FUntitled-design-1-2.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fwho-loses-when-fcra-licences-get-cancelled%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20nonprofits%20in%20India%20continue%20to%20lose%20their%20FCRA%20licences%2C%20the%20impact%20is%20being%20felt%20most%20sharply%20by%20their%20staff%2C%20the%20people%20they%20serve%2C%20and%20society%20at%20large.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fwho-loses-when-fcra-licences-get-cancelled%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Econ%20Dept%20Says%20Ashoka%20Governing%20Body%20%E2%80%98Interference%E2%80%99%20Forcing%20Scholars%20to%20%E2%80%98Operate%20in%20Environment%20of%20Fear%E2%80%99%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F03%2F25160938%2Fashoka.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20An%20open%20letter%20by%20the%20economics%20department%20of%20Ashoka%20University%20has%20accused%20the%20university%E2%80%99s%20governing%20body%20of%20reacting%20to%20a%20scholar%E2%80%99s%20recent%20research%20paper%20in%20a%20manner%20that%20%E2%80%9Cconstitutes%20institutional%20harassment%2C%20curtails%20academic%20freedom%2C%20and%20forces%20scholars%20to%20operate%20in%20an%20environment%20of%20fear%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20matter%20pertains%20to%20a%20paper%20by%20Sabyasachi%20Das%2C%20who%20resigned%20following%20the%20university%E2%80%99s%20public%20disassociation%20from%20his%20work%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20political%20controversy%20triggered%20by%20his%20findings%20on%20%E2%80%98manipulation%E2%80%99%20in%20the%202019%20general%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20his%20resignation%2C%20a%20second%20professor%20in%20the%20economics%20department%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fpulapre-balakrishnan%5C%22%3EPulapre%20Balakrishnan%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20also%20put%20in%20his%20papers%20in%20solidarity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20statement%2C%20issued%20in%20the%20name%20of%20the%20entire%20department%20and%20posted%20on%20X%20(Twitter)%20by%20Professor%20Ashwini%20Deshpande%20on%20August%2016%2C%20publicly%20makes%20two%20demands%3A%20that%20Das%20be%20immediately%20reinstated%2C%20and%20that%20the%20university%E2%80%99s%20governing%20body%20promise%20to%20not%20use%20a%20committee%20%E2%80%9Cor%20any%20other%20structure%E2%80%9D%20to%20evaluate%20faculty%20research.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EThis%20is%20the%20official%20statement%20of%20the%20Department%20of%20Economics%20at%20Ashoka.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Frodrikdani%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%40rodrikdani%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FSonaldeDesai%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%40SonaldeDesai%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FN_Kabeer%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%40N_Kabeer%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Ftajmahalfoxtrot%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%40tajmahalfoxtrot%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Frbalakra%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%40rbalakra%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FIAFFE%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%40IAFFE%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FNF4Kaq2C19%5C%22%3Ehttps%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FNF4Kaq2C19%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Ashwini_Deshpande%20(%40_ADeshpande)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2F_ADeshpande%2Fstatus%2F1691674452713738331%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EAugust%2016%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20university%E2%80%99s%20August%201%20tweet%20distancing%20itself%20from%20Das%20was%20widely%20criticised%20by%20academics%20in%20India%20and%20abroad%2C%20the%20trigger%20for%20Das%E2%80%99%20resignation%20appears%20to%20be%20an%20attempt%20by%20its%20governing%20body%20to%20%E2%80%98investigate%E2%80%99%20his%20recent%20paper%20and%20%E2%80%93%20according%20to%20university%20sources%20%E2%80%93%20get%20him%20to%20alter%20his%20title%20and%20abstract%2C%20at%20the%20very%20least.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20economics%20department%20statement%20says%20that%20%E2%80%9CProf.%20Das%20did%20not%20violate%20any%20accepted%20norm%20of%20academic%20practice%2C%E2%80%9D%20and%20adds%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAcademic%20research%20is%20professionally%20evaluated%20through%20a%20process%20of%20peer%20review.%20The%20Governing%20Body%E2%80%99s%20interference%20in%20this%20process%20to%20investigate%20the%20merits%20of%20his%20recent%20study%20constitutes%20institutional%20harassment%2C%20curtails%20academic%20freedom%2C%20and%20forces%20scholars%20to%20operate%20in%20an%20environment%20of%20fear.%20We%20condemn%20this%20in%20the%20strongest%20terms%20and%20refuse%20as%20a%20collective%20to%20cooperate%20in%20any%20future%20attempt%20to%20evaluate%20the%20research%20of%20individual%20economics%20faculty%20members%20by%20the%20governing%20body.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20university%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ashoka.edu.in%2Froles%2Fleadership-team%2F%3Ffilterby%3D320%5C%22%3Egoverning%20body%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20several%20of%20its%20promoters%20as%20members%2C%20amongst%20whom%20the%20two%20most%20prominent%20are%20Pramath%20Raj%20Sinha%20and%20Ashish%20Dhawan.%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20reached%20out%20to%20them%2C%20and%20to%20the%20vice%20chancellor%20for%20a%20response%20to%20the%20economics%20department%E2%80%99s%20statement%20and%20this%20story%20will%20be%20updated%20as%20and%20when%20they%20reply.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStating%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Coffer%20of%20resignation%20by%20our%20colleague%20Prof.%20Sabyasachi%20Das%20and%20its%20hasty%20acceptance%20by%20the%20university%20has%20deeply%20ruptured%20the%20faith%20that%20we%20in%20the%20faculty%20of%20the%20department%20of%20economics%2C%20our%20colleagues%2C%20our%20students%2C%20and%20well-wishers%20of%20Ashoka%20University%20everywhere%2C%20had%20reposed%20in%20the%20university%E2%80%99s%20leadership%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20faculty%20set%20a%20deadline%20of%20August%2023%20to%20address%20its%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CUnless%20these%20questions%20regarding%20basic%20academic%20freedoms%20are%20resolved%20before%20the%20start%20of%20the%20Monsoon%202023%20semester%2C%20faculty%20members%20of%20the%20department%20will%20find%20themselves%20unable%20to%20carry%20forward%20their%20teaching%20obligations%20in%20the%20spirit%20of%20critical%20enquiry%20and%20the%20fearless%20pursuit%20of%20truth%20that%20characterise%20our%20classrooms.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20English%20and%20creative%20writing%20departments%20of%20Ashoka%20University%20have%20also%20released%20a%20statement%20in%20solidarity%20with%20the%20Economics%20Department%2C%20stipulating%20the%20same%20demands.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20hope%2C%20too%2C%20that%20Ashoka%E2%80%99s%20official%20social%20media%20handles%20will%20cease%20putting%20out%20statements%20discrediting%20academic%20research%20by%20its%20faculty%20members%20in%20the%20future%2C%E2%80%9D%20they%20write.%20A%20failure%20to%20meet%20these%20demands%20would%20result%20in%20the%20two%20departments%20joining%20the%20economics%20department%20in%20its%20boycott%20of%20classes%20during%20the%20monsoon%202023%20semester.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOther%20faculty%20members%20raise%20concerns%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20its%20website%2C%20%E2%80%9CAshoka%20University%20is%20India%E2%80%99s%20leading%20Liberal%20Arts%20and%20Sciences%20University%20providing%20a%20distinctive%20interdisciplinary%20liberal%20education%20at%20par%20with%20the%20best%20universities%20in%20the%20world.%E2%80%9D%20But%20recent%20events%20have%20cast%20a%20shadow%20over%20these%20claims.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20separate%20statement%20by%2082%20faculty%20members%2C%20drafted%20before%20Das%E2%80%99s%20resignation%20had%20been%20accepted%2C%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CFree%20thought%20within%20universities%20in%20India%20is%20in%20crisis%20today%2C%20largely%20because%20of%20the%20near-absolute%20intolerance%20of%20critique%E2%80%A6.%20To%20stifle%20critique%20is%20to%20poison%20the%20life-blood%20of%20pedagogy%3B%20consequently%2C%20it%20is%20to%20damage%20whatever%20future%20our%20students%20might%20have%20as%20serious%20thinkers.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20statement%2C%20signed%20by%20Amit%20Chaudhuri%2C%20Rita%20Kothari%2C%20Ratul%20Lahkar%2C%20Deepak%20Mehta%2C%20Nayanjot%20Lahiri%2C%20Saikat%20Majumdar%2C%20S.M.%20Bhattacharjee%2C%20Aparna%20Vaidik%2C%20Rajendra%20Bhatia%2C%20Mukul%20Sharma%2C%20Madhavi%20Menon%2C%20Bikram%20Phookan%2C%20Pulapre%20Balakrishnan%20and%2069%20others%2C%20says%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CRecent%20events%20around%20a%20paper%20published%20by%20Professor%20Sabyasachi%20Das%20are%20a%20reminder%20that%20the%20crisis%20is%20an%20ongoing%20and%20deep%20one%2C%20with%20implications%20for%20every%20academic%20working%20at%20Ashoka%20University%20and%2C%20for%20that%20matter%2C%20in%20India%E2%80%A6%20It%20is%20not%20a%20crisis%20that%20will%20go%20away%20by%20wishing%20that%20papers%20like%20Professor%20Das%E2%80%99%20will%20not%20be%20written%20in%20the%20future%2C%20because%20that%20is%20not%20a%20realistic%20possibility%20in%20a%20working%20institution.%20It%20will%20not%20be%20solved%20by%20apologies%20and%20resignations.%20It%20has%20to%20be%20addressed%20with%20academic%20freedom%20constituting%20the%20core%20of%20our%20position%20with%20regard%20to%20the%20crisis.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20statement%20notes%20that%20though%20the%20university%20had%20drafted%20and%20adopted%20a%20document%20for%20academic%20freedom%20in%202021%2C%20it%20has%20been%20%E2%80%9Cbewildering%20to%20witness%20events%20unfold%20in%20the%20last%20two%20weeks%20that%20are%20directly%20related%20to%20academic%20freedom%20in%20a%20way%20that%20makes%20no%20reference%20to%20this%20document%20and%20behaves%2C%20to%20all%20purposes%2C%20as%20if%20it%20does%20not%20exist%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20signatories%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9Call%20responses%20to%20the%20matter%20of%20what%20may%20or%20may%20not%20be%20admissible%20in%20research%20and%20academic%20practice%20at%20Ashoka%20University%E2%80%9D%20should%20be%20handled%20as%20per%20the%20guidelines%20set%20out%20in%20that%20document%2C%20%E2%80%9Cwhich%2C%20rather%20than%20any%20tweet%20or%20individual%20opinion%2C%20expresses%20the%20university%E2%80%99s%20position%20on%20this%20all-important%20subject%E2%80%9D.%20They%20also%20said%20that%20the%20Committee%20for%20Academic%20Freedom%2C%20which%20the%20document%20had%20proposed%20be%20set%20up%20soon%2C%20%E2%80%9Cbe%20created%20immediately%E2%80%9D%20to%20bring%20%E2%80%9Cmuch-needed%20transparency%20and%20procedural%20fairness%20whenever%20such%20issues%20arise.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBalakrishnan%20has%20since%20also%20resigned%20from%20the%20university.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20Ashoka%20vice-chancellor%20Somak%20Raychaudhury%20said%20on%20Monday%20that%20the%20university%20%E2%80%9Caffords%20its%20faculty%20and%20students%20the%20most%20enabling%20environment%20for%20academic%20freedom%20at%20an%20institution%20of%20higher%20education%2C%E2%80%9D%20and%20that%20this%20%E2%80%9Cacademic%20freedom%20also%20applied%20to%20Mr.%20Das%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20charge%20levelled%20by%20the%20economics%20department%20casts%20doubts%20on%20this%20assurance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20reported%2C%20the%20university%E2%80%99s%20stand%20on%20Das%20has%20drawn%20criticism%20from%20students%20and%20academics%2C%20especially%20given%20the%20track%20record%20of%20how%20it%20had%20handled%20its%20reputed%20vice%20chancellor%20Pratap%20Bhanu%20Mehta%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fpratap-bhanu-mehta-resigns-as-professor-at-ashoka-university%23%3A~%3Atext%3DIn%252520a%252520letter%252520to%252520students%2CVC%252520rather%252520than%252520stop%252520writing.%5C%22%3Ewhen%20he%20was%20both%20nudged%20and%20persuaded%20to%20resign%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20March%202021%20due%20to%20his%20media%20writings%20on%20the%20politics%20of%20the%20ruling%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20critic%20called%20Ashoka%E2%80%99s%20comment%20on%20Das%E2%80%99%20paper%20an%20example%20of%C2%A0%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theindiacable.com%2Fi%2F135712802%2Fashoka-universitys-response-to-its-own-faculty-is-democratic-backsliding-in-academia%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98democratic%20backsliding%20in%20academia%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202017%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fashoka-university-resignations-kashmir%5C%22%3Eallegations%20had%20been%20levelled%20by%20the%20faculty%20council%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20university%E2%80%99s%20founders%20had%20asked%20two%20members%20of%20the%20non-teaching%20staff%20%E2%80%93%20deputy%20manager%20of%20academic%20affairs%20Sau